Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that the inner product on `X × Y` satisfies the norm equivalence property.

The inner product is defined as `⟪(x, y), (x', y')⟫ = ⟪x, x'⟫ + ⟪y, y'⟫`.

For the pair `(x, y)`, the inner product with itself is `⟪(x, y), (x, y)⟫ = ⟪x, x⟫ + ⟪y, y⟫`.

I have hypotheses `_hx` and `_hy` that give me bounds for `X` and `Y` respectively (though I notice `_hy` incorrectly uses `X` instead of `Y`, which seems like a bug in the setup).

The norm on the product space `X × Y` is the max norm by default: `‖(x, y)‖ = max ‖x‖ ‖y‖`.

Let me establish the inequalities using the available hypotheses about the components.

```lean
instance : AdjointSpace 𝕜 (X×Y) where
  inner := fun (x,y) (x',y') => ⟪x,x'⟫_𝕜 + ⟪y,y'⟫_𝕜
  inner_top_equiv_norm := by
    have ⟨cx,dx,hcx,hdx,hx⟩ := inner_top_equiv_norm (𝕜:=𝕜) (E:=X)
    have ⟨cy,dy,hcy,hdy,hy⟩ := inner_top_equiv_norm (𝕜:=𝕜) (E:=Y)
    apply Exists.intro (min cx cy / 2)
    apply Exists.intro (dx + dy)
    constructor
    · positivity
    constructor
    · positivity
    · intro (x,y)
      simp only [Inner.inner, Prod.norm_def, sq_max_sq]
      constructor
      · have hx' := (hx x).1
        have hy' := (hy y).1
        calc
          min cx cy / 2 • max (‖x‖ ^ 2) (‖y‖ ^ 2)
            ≤ min cx cy / 2 • (‖x‖ ^ 2 + ‖y‖ ^ 2) := by
              rw [smul_eq_mul, smul_eq_mul]
              apply mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_left _ (by positivity)
              cases' le_total (‖x‖ ^ 2) (‖y‖ ^ 2) with h h
              · simp [max_eq_right h]; linarith [sq_nonneg ‖x‖]
              · simp [max_eq_left h]; linarith [sq_nonneg ‖y‖]
          _ ≤ min cx cy • ‖x‖ ^ 2 / 2 + min cx cy • ‖y‖ ^ 2 / 2 := by ring
          _ ≤ cx • ‖x‖ ^ 2 / 2 + cy • ‖y‖ ^ 2 / 2 := by
              apply add_le_add <;> { rw [smul_eq_mul, smul_eq_mul]; apply mul_le_mul_of_nonneg_right; apply min_le_left <|> apply min_le_right; positivity }
          _ ≤ re ⟪x, x⟫_𝕜 / 2 + re ⟪y, y⟫_𝕜 / 2 := by linarith
          _ = re (⟪x, x⟫_𝕜 + ⟪y, y⟫_𝕜) / 2 := by simp [add_div]
          _ ≤ re (⟪x, x⟫_𝕜 + ⟪y, y⟫_𝕜) := by linarith [inner_self_nonneg (x := x), inner_self_nonneg (x := y)]
      · have hx' := (hx x).2
        have hy' := (hy y).2
        calc
          re (⟪x, x⟫_𝕜 + ⟪y, y⟫_𝕜)
            = re ⟪x, x⟫_𝕜 + re ⟪y, y⟫_𝕜 := by simp
          _ ≤ dx • ‖x‖ ^ 2 + dy • ‖y‖ ^ 2 := add_le_add hx' hy'
          _ ≤ (dx + dy) • max (‖x‖ ^ 2) (‖y‖ ^ 2) := by
              rw [add_smul]
              apply add_le_add <;> { apply smul_le_smul_of_nonneg_left; apply le_max_left <|> apply le_max_right; positivity }
  conj_symm := by simp[mul_comm, add_comm, conj_symm]
  add_left := by simp[add_mul, add_assoc, add_comm, add_left_comm, add_left]
  smul_left := by simp[mul_assoc, mul_add, smul_left]
